CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 12, 1957, page A15, reads: "Pittsburgh's Chic Ethel Littlejohn and Nellie Barron were two of the seven hand picked models taking part in the fashion show. Both are noted for their exquisite gowns and made a big splash at the Saturday night fete. - All Photos by Teenie Harris."Nellie Barron was the wife of George "Crip Barron", a well known numbers banker in the Hill District.
TitMainTitle: Two women, Ethel Littlejohn and Nellie Barron, modeling cocktail dresses and fur stoles, posed interior with marble paneling and terrazzo checkered floor for the National Council of Negro Women fashion show
